NAME
       cat - print file contents

SYNOPSIS
       cat FILE

DESCRIPTION
       Print the contents of FILE to the terminal.

       FILE may be a path such as 'projects/README.txt'. Trying
       to read a directory or a file that does not exist shows
       an error.

SEE ALSO
       ls(1), cd(1), man(1)

